docs.abstract: The Treasury Department accused seven Ukrainians of working with a Russian agent “to spread misleading and unsubstantiated allegations” about President-elect Joseph R. Biden Jr.
docs.snippet: The Treasury Department accused seven Ukrainians of working with a Russian agent “to spread misleading and unsubstantiated allegations” about President-elect Joseph R. Biden Jr.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration imposed sanctions on Monday against seven Ukrainians — including two who assisted President Trump’s personal lawyer Rudolph W. Giuliani — for being part of what it called “a Russia-linked foreign influence network” that spread “fraudulent and unsubstantiated allegations” about President-elect Joseph R. Biden Jr. during the 2020 campaign.

headline.main: U.S. Imposes Sanctions on Ukrainians Linked to Giuliani for Election Disinformation
headline.print_headline: 7 Ukrainians Are Penalized for Election Deceit

docs.abstract: China’s national legislature disclosed plans for a law that would make it extremely difficult for Beijing’s critics to hold elective office in Hong Kong.
docs.snippet: China’s national legislature disclosed plans for a law that would make it extremely difficult for Beijing’s critics to hold elective office in Hong Kong.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — When Beijing set out last summer to quash resistance to its rule in Hong Kong, it imposed a national security law that empowered the authorities to arrest scores of democracy advocates and sent a chill over the city.

headline.main: Demanding Loyalty, China Moves to Overhaul Hong Kong Elections
headline.print_headline: China Moves To Overhaul Election Law In Hong Kong

docs.abstract: The justices are about to consider whether the Voting Rights Act applies to policies that restrict the vote.
docs.snippet: The justices are about to consider whether the Voting Rights Act applies to policies that restrict the vote.
docs.lead_paragraph: When the Supreme Court on Monday rejected Pennsylvania Republicans’ after-the-fact effort to invalidate late-arriving mailed ballots, it was tempting to suppose that the country’s courthouse doors had finally closed on this most litigated of presidential elections.

headline.main: The Supreme Court Is Not Finished With Elections

docs.abstract: The party of President Nayib Bukele is set to take a sweeping majority in El Salvador’s Congress, giving the populist leader broad new powers.
docs.snippet: The party of President Nayib Bukele is set to take a sweeping majority in El Salvador’s Congress, giving the populist leader broad new powers.
docs.lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — El Salvador’s populist president was poised on Monday to claim a resounding victory in the country’s legislative elections, dealing a crushing blow to establishment parties and granting the young leader, who has been accused of authoritarian tendencies, a powerful new mandate.

headline.main: After El Salvador Election, Bukele Is on Verge of Near-Total Control

docs.abstract: New proposals by the G.O.P.-controlled Legislature have targeted Sunday voting, part of a raft of measures that could reduce the impact of Black voters in the state.
docs.snippet: New proposals by the G.O.P.-controlled Legislature have targeted Sunday voting, part of a raft of measures that could reduce the impact of Black voters in the state.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAVANNAH, Ga. — Sundays are always special at the St. Philip Monumental A.M.E. church. But in October, the pews are often more packed, the sermon a bit more urgent and the congregation more animated, and eager for what will follow: piling into church vans and buses — though some prefer to walk — and heading to the polls.

headline.main: In Georgia, Republicans Take Aim at Role of Black Churches in Elections
headline.print_headline: Georgia Bills Target Black Church Voting Drives

docs.abstract: The central government is likely to bypass local officials, just as it did with last year’s national security law.
docs.snippet: The central government is likely to bypass local officials, just as it did with last year’s national security law.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — China’s Communist Party already wields outsized influence over Hong Kong’s political landscape. Its allies have long controlled a committee that handpicks the territory’s leader. Its loyalists dominate the Hong Kong legislature. It ousted four of the city’s elected opposition lawmakers last year.

headline.main: ‘Patriots’ Only: Beijing Plans Overhaul of Hong Kong’s Elections
headline.print_headline: Beijing Plans to Filter Candidates Before Hong Kong Elections

docs.abstract: Nayib Bukele, who has drawn criticism abroad for his strongman displays, is expected to expand his mandate in legislative elections that could deliver his party a decisive victory.

docs.lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — In his first two years in office, El Salvador’s president marched soldiers into the country’s legislature, defied Supreme Court rulings, published photos of barely clothed gang members crammed together on a prison floor and dispatched the military to detain anyone breaking quarantine.

headline.main: Salvador’s Leader, Combative but Popular, May Tighten Grip in Elections
